<p><strong>Christmas &amp; New Year Celebrations<br /></strong></p>
<p>Leave behind the UK's dull, grey, damp December and join us instead for a proper <strong>'White Christmas' in the Alps!</strong> All our chalets and Chalet Hotels have a Christmas tree and most have log fires to add to the festive atmosphere, so combined with great food, good company, and no cooking or washing up, where would you rather be?<br /><br />All our chalets and Chalet Hotels feature a full traditional Christmas Turkey Dinner on Christmas Day, with mince pies and Christmas pudding to follow, crackers, and a pre-dinner glass of Champagne. Santa will also drop in at some stage if you have children aged 8 or under in your party!<br /><br />On New Year's Eve, all our chalets and Chalet Hotels serve a special Celebration Menu, preceded by a glass of Champagne. After dinner join the resort festivities, generally with fireworks to see in the New Year.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span class="geolocation-title">Some additional Information</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Free Places in our Chalets &amp; Chalet Hotels</strong></p>
<p>If you are a group of 7 or more in a chalet, you may be entitled to free group places and/or list passes. See our <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/information/groups/#freechaletplaces" title="Ski groups chalet free places">Ski Groups</a> page for details.</p>
<p><strong>Singles</strong></p>
<p>Some of our chalets and Chalet Hotels have single rooms. These are limited in number, so book early. Alternatively, you can pay a supplement to keep a twin or double room for sole occupancy. For more information on hotels with single or double rooms for sole use without a supplement, see our <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/article/2010/single-savers/" title="Ski single savers">Ski Single Savers</a> page.</p>
<p><strong>Exclusive Use</strong></p>
<p>Entire chalets or Chalet Hotels can be booked for exclusive use for your group or family. If you cannot fill all the advertised minimum occupancy beds, a supplement is payable that replaces the total room under occupancy supplements.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Room Under-Occupancy</strong></p>
<p>Supplements apply when a room is not used to its full, costed capacity, for example if two people book a three-bedded room (at least the minimum number stated must be booked). See <a href="/legal/terms-conditions" title="terms and conditions">terms and conditions</a> for details.</p>
<p><strong>Floor plans<br /></strong></p>
<p>Floor plans for most of our chalets, Xtra Chalets and Chalet Hotels can be found under the 'Accommodation Summary' of the relevant property where available.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
</div>]]></bodyText>
